Reverse the string "Hello World":
txt = "Hello World"[::-1]
print(txt)


 def my_function(x):
  return x[::-1]

mytxt = my_function("I wonder how this text looks like backwards")

print(mytxt)

Slice the string starting at the end of the string and move backwards.
Slice the String
def my_function(x):
  return x [::-1]

mytxt = my_function("I wonder how this text looks like backwards")

print(mytxt)

Return the backward String
Return the String
def my_function(x):
  return x[::-1]

mytxt = my_function("I wonder how this text looks like backwards")

print(mytxt )
